<Vertical id="RefFieldDemo" title="Ref Field Access">

  <Markdown>
## Field-Specific Access

By default, Ref calls `getValue()` on the target. The `field` attribute lets you
access a specific field directly, effectively converting any field to a displayable value.

### Accessing the Value Field Directly

Type something:
  </Markdown>

  <LineInput id="text_input" />

  <Markdown>
**Using getValue (default):**
  </Markdown>
  <Ref target="text_input" />

  <Markdown>
**Using field="value" (same result for LineInput):**
  </Markdown>
  <Ref target="text_input" field="value" />

  <Markdown>
### LLM Feedback State

The LLMFeedback component has both `value` (the feedback text) and `state` (loading status).
You can access either field:
  </Markdown>

  <TextArea id="essay" rows="2" placeholder="Write something for feedback..." />
  <LLMFeedback id="feedback_demo" />
  <ActionButton label="Get Feedback">
    <LLMAction target="feedback_demo">
      Give brief feedback on: <Ref target="essay" />
    </LLMAction>
  </ActionButton>

  <Markdown>
**Feedback value:**
  </Markdown>
  <Ref target="feedback_demo" field="value" />

  <Markdown>
**Feedback state:**
  </Markdown>
  <Ref target="feedback_demo" field="state" />

</Vertical>
